text.section:
To set front-foot assessment rates, the municipal authority may:
Classify any property according to its use;
Determine a fair and reasonable frontage length for:
Any corner lot fronting on more than one street;
Any irregular shaped lot fronting on more than one street;
Any shallow lot fronting on more than one street;
Any agricultural property; or
Any small acreage; and
Change the classifications or the front-foot assessment rates from year to year, but the rate for all property assessed in the municipality for any year shall be uniform within each classification.
